    "recap_headline": "East Carolina University",
    "recap_text": "GREENVILLE, N.C.\u00a0\u2013\nEast Carolina (14-8-1, 1-0 American) opened conference play with a gritty 3-2 victory over UAB (13-9, 0-1 American) on Friday night at Lewis Field\u00a0in\u00a0Clark-LeClair Stadium, leaning on strong pitching and\u00a0timely\u00a0hitting to secure the win.\nIn a game defined by pitching and defensive plays, both teams threatened early. UAB put pressure on the Pirates in the opening innings with deep fly balls, but right fielder\nDavin Whitaker\ndelivered a standout defensive performance, including a home run robbery in right-center that kept the Blazers off the scoreboard.\nUAB broke through first in the top of the third inning, using a leadoff double and a sacrifice fly to take a 1-0 lead.\nThe Pirates answered\u00a0immediately\u00a0in the bottom half of the inning. Whitaker recorded ECU's first hit of the night with a single, and\nGrady Lenahan\nfollowed with a double to put runners in scoring position.\nBraden Burress\nthen brought home the tying run with an RBI groundout, evening the score at 1-1.\nEast Carolina took the lead in the fourth inning.\nJack Herring\nsingled and advanced to third on a pair of wild pitches. With two outs,\nColby Wallace\ndelivered a clutch RBI single to left field on a 3-0 count, giving the Pirates a 2-1 advantage.\nStarter\nEthan Norby\nnavigated through trouble in the fifth inning, escaping a\u00a0bases-loaded jam with a strikeout to preserve the lead. The right-hander turned in a strong outing, earning the win after tossing 6.0 innings, allowing just one run on five hits while striking out six.\nAfter a quiet stretch through the middle innings, ECU added an insurance run in the seventh.\nCarlos Jacome\nsingled to start the inning and later came around to score on a two-out RBI single from\nWalker Barron\n, extending the lead to 3-1.\nThe Pirates' defense continued to shine throughout the night, highlighted by Whitaker's play in the outfield and a key infield double play that helped limit UAB's opportunities. ECU also held the Blazers to 0-for-6 with runners in scoring position while stranding 10 runners on base.\nOut of the bullpen,\nJoseph Webb\nprovided two scoreless innings with a pair of strikeouts, allowing just one hit.\nUAB made things interesting in the ninth inning, capitalizing on an error and a wild pitch to cut the deficit to 3-2. However,\nSean Jenkins\nsettled in and struck out three batters in the frame to secure his third save of the season.\nSix different Pirates recorded hits in the win, with Wallace and Barron each delivering key two-out RBIs.\nEast Carolina will look to clinch the series on Saturday afternoon, with first pitch scheduled for 4:00 p.m. EST.",
